# Supported commit types: feat, fix, chore, refactor, perf, remove, revert, docs, test, style, build, ci
# Example: feat(core): add new feature [release:minor]

# Conventional Commit (international standard: conventionalcommits.org)
# Use English type keywords only (global convention for tooling)

<type>[scope][!]: <short summary>

# Common types (English – required by the spec):
#   feat      → minor version
#   fix       → patch version
#   docs      → documentation only
#   style     → formatting, no code change
#   refactor  → code change, no behavior change
#   perf      → performance improvement
#   test      → adding/fixing tests
#   build     → build system or dependencies
#   ci        → CI configuration
#   chore     → maintenance (no user impact)
#   revert    → revert previous commit
#
# Add ! after type/scope for breaking changes (major version)
# Example: feat(api)!: or fix!:

<detailed body – WHAT + WHY + HOW>
